The paper deals with communication channels and strategies for relay channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a distributed compress and forward strategy, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper discusses the use of antennas and space-time codes, which are topics covered in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an end-to-end antenna selection strategy, which involves optimizing the transmission of signals, a topic that falls under the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
